<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<%- include('layouts/header'); -%>
   <body style="background-color: #FEFBE4;">   
   <%- include('layouts/heading'); -%>
   


    <main>
       <div class="container marketing">                     
           <h1>Cookie Policy</h1>
    <p class="last-updated"><strong>Last Updated:</strong> <%= new Date().toLocaleDateString('en-US', { year: 'numeric', month: 'long', day: 'numeric' }) %></p>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
        <p><%= company.name %> ("we," "us," or "our") uses cookies and similar tracking technologies on our <%= company.serviceType %> (the "Service"). This Cookie Policy explains what cookies are, how we use them, and your choices regarding their use.</p>
        <p>By using our Service, you consent to our use of cookies in accordance with this policy. This Cookie Policy is part of and incorporated into our <a href="<%= links.privacyPolicy %>"  target="_blank">Privacy Policy</a>.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>2. What Are Cookies?</h2>
        <p>Cookies are small text files that are placed on your device (computer, smartphone, tablet) when you visit a website. They are widely used to make websites work efficiently, provide a better user experience, and provide information to website owners.</p>
        
        <h3>Types of Cookies by Duration:</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Session Cookies:</strong> Temporary cookies that are deleted when you close your browser</li>
            <li><strong>Persistent Cookies:</strong> Cookies that remain on your device for a set period or until you delete them</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Types of Cookies by Origin:</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>First-party Cookies:</strong> Set by the website you're visiting (<%= company.domain %>)</li>
            <li><strong>Third-party Cookies:</strong> Set by services used on our website (analytics, advertising partners)</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>3. How We Use Cookies</h2>
        <p>We use cookies for the following purposes:</p>

        <div class="cookie-category essential-cookies">
            <h3>Essential Cookies <span class="cookie-type-badge badge-essential">Always Active</span></h3>
            <p>These cookies are necessary for the website to function and cannot be disabled. They are usually set in response to your actions, such as setting privacy preferences, logging in, or filling out forms.</p>
        </div>

        <% if (cookieTypes.functional) { %>
        <div class="cookie-category">
            <h3>Functional Cookies <span class="cookie-type-badge badge-functional">Optional</span></h3>
            <p>These cookies enable enhanced functionality and personalization, such as remembering your preferences, language selection, or region.</p>
        </div>
        <% } %>

        <% if (cookieTypes.analytics) { %>
        <div class="cookie-category analytics-cookies">
            <h3>Analytics Cookies <span class="cookie-type-badge badge-analytics">Optional</span></h3>
            <p>These cookies help us understand how visitors interact with our website by collecting and reporting information anonymously. This helps us improve our Service.</p>
        </div>
        <% } %>

        <% if (cookieTypes.marketing) { %>
        <div class="cookie-category marketing-cookies">
            <h3>Marketing/Advertising Cookies <span class="cookie-type-badge badge-marketing">Optional</span></h3>
            <p>These cookies are used to deliver advertisements relevant to you and your interests. They may also limit the number of times you see an advertisement and help measure the effectiveness of advertising campaigns.</p>
        </div>
        <% } %>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>4. Cookies We Use</h2>
        
        <h3>Essential Cookies</h3>
        <table class="cookie-table">
            <thead>
                <tr>
                    <th>Cookie Name</th>
                    <th>Provider</th>
                    <th>Purpose</th>
                    <th>Expiry</th>
                </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
                <% essentialCookies.forEach(cookie => { %>
                <tr>
                    <td><code><%= cookie.name %></code></td>
                    <td><%= cookie.provider %></td>
                    <td><%= cookie.purpose %></td>
                    <td><%= cookie.expiry %></td>
                </tr>
                <% }) %>
            </tbody>
        </table>

        <% if (cookieTypes.functional && functionalCookies.length > 0) { %>
        <h3>Functional Cookies</h3>
        <table class="cookie-table">
            <thead>
                <tr>
                    <th>Cookie Name</th>
                    <th>Provider</th>
                    <th>Purpose</th>
                    <th>Expiry</th>
                </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
                <% functionalCookies.forEach(cookie => { %>
                <tr>
                    <td><code><%= cookie.name %></code></td>
                    <td><%= cookie.provider %></td>
                    <td><%= cookie.purpose %></td>
                    <td><%= cookie.expiry %></td>
                </tr>
                <% }) %>
            </tbody>
        </table>
        <% } %>

        <% if (cookieTypes.analytics && analyticsCookies.length > 0) { %>
        <h3>Analytics Cookies</h3>
        <table class="cookie-table">
            <thead>
                <tr>
                    <th>Cookie Name</th>
                    <th>Provider</th>
                    <th>Purpose</th>
                    <th>Expiry</th>
                </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
                <% analyticsCookies.forEach(cookie => { %>
                <tr>
                    <td><code><%= cookie.name %></code></td>
                    <td><%= cookie.provider %></td>
                    <td><%= cookie.purpose %></td>
                    <td><%= cookie.expiry %></td>
                </tr>
                <% }) %>
            </tbody>
        </table>
        <% } %>

        <% if (cookieTypes.marketing && marketingCookies.length > 0) { %>
        <h3>Marketing Cookies</h3>
        <table class="cookie-table">
            <thead>
                <tr>
                    <th>Cookie Name</th>
                    <th>Provider</th>
                    <th>Purpose</th>
                    <th>Expiry</th>
                </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
                <% marketingCookies.forEach(cookie => { %>
                <tr>
                    <td><code><%= cookie.name %></code></td>
                    <td><%= cookie.provider %></td>
                    <td><%= cookie.purpose %></td>
                    <td><%= cookie.expiry %></td>
                </tr>
                <% }) %>
            </tbody>
        </table>
        <% } %>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>5. Third-Party Services</h2>
        <p>We use the following third-party services that may set cookies:</p>
        <ul>
            <% thirdPartyServices.forEach(service => { %>
            <li>
                <strong><%= service.name %>:</strong> <%= service.description %>
                <% if (service.privacyUrl) { %>
                (<a href="<%= service.privacyUrl %>" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Privacy Policy</a>)
                <% } %>
            </li>
            <% }) %>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>6. Your Cookie Choices</h2>
        
        <div class="manage-cookies-box">
            <h3>Cookie Consent Management</h3>
            <p>You can manage your cookie preferences at any time:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Cookie Settings:</strong> Click the "Cookie Settings" link in the footer of any page</li>
                <li><strong>First Visit:</strong> Use our cookie consent banner when you first visit our site</li>
                <li><strong>Account Settings:</strong> Registered users can manage preferences in account settings</li>
            </ul>
            <% if (features.cookieSettingsUrl) { %>
            <p><a href="<%= features.cookieSettingsUrl %>"  target="_blank" class="cookie-settings-link">Manage Cookie Settings</a></p>
            <% } %>
        </div>

        <h3>Browser Cookie Controls</h3>
        <div class="browser-settings">
            <p>You can also control cookies through your browser settings. Here's how for popular browsers:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Chrome:</strong> Settings → Privacy and security → Cookies and other site data</li>
                <li><strong>Firefox:</strong> Settings → Privacy & Security → Cookies and Site Data</li>
                <li><strong>Safari:</strong> Preferences → Privacy → Manage Website Data</li>
                <li><strong>Edge:</strong> Settings → Privacy, search, and services → Cookies and site permissions</li>
            </ul>
            <p><strong>Note:</strong> Blocking all cookies may impact your experience on our Service.</p>
        </div>

        <h3>Opt-Out Links</h3>
        <p>You can opt out of specific third-party cookies:</p>
        <ul>
            <% if (cookieTypes.analytics) { %>
            <li>Google Analytics: <a href="https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google Analytics Opt-out Browser Add-on</a></li>
            <% } %>
            <% if (cookieTypes.marketing) { %>
            <li>Google Ads: <a href="https://adssettings.google.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google Ads Settings</a></li>
            <li>Facebook: <a href="https://www.facebook.com/ads/preferences" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Facebook Ad Preferences</a></li>
            <% } %>
            <li>General opt-out: <a href="https://optout.aboutads.info" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Digital Advertising Alliance Opt-Out</a></li>
            <li>EU users: <a href="https://www.youronlinechoices.eu" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Your Online Choices</a></li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>7. Do Not Track Signals</h2>
        <p><%= features.respectDNT ? 
            'We respect Do Not Track (DNT) browser signals. When we detect a DNT signal, we do not load analytics or marketing cookies.' : 
            'We do not currently respond to Do Not Track (DNT) browser signals. However, you can still manage cookies using the methods described above.' %>
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>8. Cookies and Personal Data</h2>
        <p>Some cookies we use may collect personal data. For information about how we handle personal data, please see our <a href="<%= links.privacyPolicy %>"  target="_blank">Privacy Policy</a>.</p>
        <p>We process cookie data based on:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Consent:</strong> For optional cookies (functional, analytics, marketing)</li>
            <li><strong>Legitimate interests:</strong> For essential cookies necessary to provide the Service</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <% if (features.childrenPrivacy) { %>
    <div class="section">
        <h2>9. Children's Privacy</h2>
        <p>Our Service is not directed to children under <%= company.minimumAge %>. We do not knowingly use cookies to collect data from children under <%= company.minimumAge %>.</p>
    </div>
    <% } %>

    <div class="section">
        <h2><%= features.childrenPrivacy ? '10' : '9' %>. International Transfers</h2>
        <p>Some of our third-party cookie providers may transfer data internationally. These transfers are protected by appropriate safeguards, including:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Standard contractual clauses approved by the European Commission</li>
            <li>Privacy Shield certification (where applicable)</li>
            <li>Adequacy decisions</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2><%= features.childrenPrivacy ? '11' : '10' %>. Updates to This Policy</h2>
        <p>We may update this Cookie Policy from time to time to reflect changes in our practices or legal requirements. We will notify you of any material changes by:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Updating the "Last Updated" date</li>
            <li>Posting a notice on our Service</li>
            <% if (features.emailNotifications) { %>
            <li>Emailing registered users for significant changes</li>
            <% } %>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2><%= features.childrenPrivacy ? '12' : '11' %>. Contact Us</h2>
        <p>If you have questions about our use of cookies, please contact us:</p>
        <div class="contact-box">
            <p><strong><%= company.name %></strong></p>
            <p>Email: <a href="mailto:<%= company.privacyEmail %>"><%= company.privacyEmail %></a></p>
            <p>Address: <%= company.address %></p>
            <% if (company.dpo) { %>
            <p>Data Protection Officer: <%= company.dpo.name %> - <a href="mailto:<%= company.dpo.email %>"><%= company.dpo.email %></a></p>
            <% } %>
        </div>
        
        <p>You also have the right to lodge a complaint with your local data protection authority about our use of cookies.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>Cookie Glossary</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>HTTP Cookie:</strong> A small piece of data sent from a website and stored on your device</li>
            <li><strong>Session ID:</strong> A unique identifier assigned to a user session</li>
            <li><strong>Pixel Tag:</strong> A tiny image used to track user behavior</li>
            <li><strong>Local Storage:</strong> A web storage method that stores data with no expiration time</li>
            <li><strong>Flash Cookie:</strong> Data stored by Adobe Flash plugin (being phased out)</li>
        </ul>
    </div>               
       </div>
    </main>

    <%- include('layouts/footer'); -%>
   </body>
</html>

